Intent Data and Account Intelligence

One of the most powerful shifts in B2B lead generation over the past several years has been the rise of intent data. Intent data tells you which companies are actively researching topics related to your product or service right now, based on their digital behavior across the web.

In 2026, leveraging intent data is no longer optional for competitive B2B campaigns. It allows you to prioritize outreach toward accounts that are already in-market, dramatically improving conversion rates and reducing wasted effort on accounts that are simply not ready.

How do you act on intent data effectively?

Prioritize accounts showing strong intent signals for your core solution categories. Align your messaging to the specific topics they are researching. Coordinate sales and marketing outreach so that when a rep reaches out, it feels timely and relevant rather than random.

